Hound — anomaly detector

Hound detects bad translations.

Examples:
	•	tower is visible but non-enterable when “stairs” were requested
	•	object looks stable but has broken collision
	•	style overlay hides critical affordances
	•	neural enhancement drifts from runtime truth

Hound owns:
	•	mismatch detection
	•	drift alerts
	•	broken affordance warnings

⸻

Sisyphus — temporal regulator

Sisyphus handles continuity through time.

A castle at t0, damaged at t1, burning at t2, repaired on branch B must remain the same identity across state changes.

Sisyphus owns:
	•	temporal consistency
	•	replay-safe transformations
