Action-space formalization

The Director Agent should never directly “make things happen” vaguely.

It should compile intent into Bridge Actions.

Bridge Action types

1. Instantiate

Create a new runtime object.

Example:

instantiate(object_class="tower", region="left_district")

2. Modify

Change attributes of an existing object.

modify(uuid="obj_147", material="blue_glass")

3. Relocate

Change transform or anchor relationship.

relocate(uuid="obj_147", anchor="hill_west")

4. Re-style

Change perceptual layer without changing operational core.

restyle(uuid="obj_147", style="gothic_noir")

5. Reconcile

Resolve semantic conflict.

reconcile(target="sky_state", policy="branch_timeline")

6. Re-project

Re-render from a new viewpoint/fidelity regime.

reproject(region="castle_interior", mode="high_detail")

7. Distill

Summarize current state back into language for the user.

distill(region="north_hill")

These actions define the bridge’s executable vocabulary.

