Semantic conflict resolution

This must be formalized inside the NSB, not left vague.

Conflict types

Direct contradiction

“Make it bright daylight” then “make it pitch black”

Ontological contradiction

“Make the stone tower liquid but still fully climbable like stone stairs”

Topological contradiction

“Put the castle both inside the mountain and visible on top of it”

Narrative contradiction

“Keep the city untouched but also show it burning from the earlier attack”

Resolution policies

Policy A — last-write wins

Useful for low-stakes aesthetic parameters.

Policy B — invariant priority

Core world rules outrank later commands.

Policy C — ask/offer branch

Fork the timeline.

Policy D — layered coexistence

Different truths at different layers.
Example: perceptually dark, physically daytime due to eclipse/storm.

Mirror should arbitrate this, with Spider maintaining coherence.

