Performance doctrine

The NSB should explicitly operate under fidelity tiers.

Tier 1 — symbolic far-field

Distant or low-salience objects:
	•	lightweight geometry
	•	low update cost
	•	semantic placeholders

Tier 2 — spatial operational mid-field

Objects near interaction range:
	•	full nav/collision
	•	explicit topology
	•	moderate detail

Tier 3 — neural high-fidelity focal field

Current focus region:
	•	rich textures
	•	cinematic motion
	•	high sensory detail
	•	responsive refinements

This gives a practical answer to latency and compute constraints.

Meaning is preserved everywhere, fidelity concentrates where attention is.

That matches your Attention Budget Ledger too.

